1) A task cannot have more than 20 subtasks

context Task
inv MaxTwentySubtasks:
    self.subtasks->size() <= 20

Through a method:

public boolean hasValidSubtaskCount() {
    return subtasks.size() <= 20;
}


2) The number of open tasks without a due date should not exceed 50

context Task
inv MaxFiftyOpenTasksWithoutDueDate:
    Task.allInstances()
        ->select(t | t.status = Status::open and t.dueDate.oclIsUndefined())
        ->size() <= 50

Through a method:

public boolean hasValidOpenTasksWithoutDueDateLimit(List<Task> tasks) {
    long count = tasks.stream()
            .filter(task -> task.getStatus() == Status.OPEN)
            .filter(task -> task.getDueDate() == null)
            .count();

    return count <= 50;
}

3)The limit for open tasks for each collaborator category is a positive integer

context CollaboratorCategory
inv PositiveOpenTaskLimit:
    self.openTaskLimit > 0

Through a method:

public boolean hasValidOpenTaskLimit() {
    return openTaskLimit > 0;
}

4) No collaborator must be overloaded

context Collaborator
inv NotOverloaded:
    self.assignedTasks->select(t | t.status = Status::open)->size() <= self.category.openTaskLimit

Through a method: 

public boolean isWithinOpenTaskLimit() {
    long openTasks = assignedTasks.stream()
            .filter(task -> task.getStatus() == Status.OPEN)
            .count();

    return openTasks <= category.getOpenTaskLimit();
}
